---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100 min-h-screen">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <header class="pt-32 pb-28 px-6 text-center max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="inline-block px-6 py-2.5 rounded-full bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 text-[#58bbc2] text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-10">
        LEADERSHIP ARCHITECTURE | OPERATIONAL RESILIENCE
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-6xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tighter leading-none mb-8 text-white">
        Burnout is a <span class="text-[#58bbc2]">Design Flaw.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-2xl text-zinc-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-6">
        We don't fix people. We fix the structures that are breaking them.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-zinc-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Mid-sized organizations are running AI-era complexity on 1995 management structures. 
        We find the structural break, fix it in 90 days, and show you the receipts.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mt-16">
        <a href="https://form.typeform.com/to/eo5W8Zio" target="_blank"
           class="px-10 py-5 bg-[#064680] hover:bg-[#2a7ca3] text-white font-semibold rounded-2xl transition text-lg">
          Start Structural Audit
        </a>
        <a href="/structural-burnout/services" 
           class="px-10 py-5 border border-zinc-700 hover:border-[#58bbc2] text-white font-semibold rounded-2xl transition text-lg">
          Book Speaking
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Crisis Section -->
    <section class="py-24 border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-8 text-white">The High Cost of Failed Bridges.</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
              Burnout isn't a wellness issue — it's an engineering failure. When you give a manager 100% of the responsibility but only 20% of the decision authority, you aren't leading. You are extracting human capacity until the bridge collapses.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-zinc-800 p-8 rounded-3xl text-center border border-orange-500/30">
              <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-orange-400">$190B</div>
              <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500 mt-3">Annual U.S. Loss</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-zinc-800 p-8 rounded-3xl text-center">
              <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#58bbc2]">53%</div>
              <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500 mt-3">Manager Burnout Rate</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-zinc-800 p-8 rounded-3xl text-center border border-[#064680]">
              <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">213%</div>
              <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500 mt-3">Replacement Cost</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Three Ways In -->
    <section class="py-24 bg-zinc-950">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-6 text-white">Three Ways In. One Direction.</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Every engagement path leads to organizational structures that stop breaking the people inside them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer note for this section -->
    <footer class="py-12 text-center text-xs text-zinc-500 border-t border-zinc-800">
      Strategic Transformations • Powered by Unbothered Resistance International
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>